blbv5orsmJ_u8v_51CXBgQ
aka Green is an eco-building dream. It's also a fun and accessible place to browse.   They have all kinds of goodies here: Yolo and other low-VOC paints, kirei board (google it, you have to see the pictures), marmoleum and other cool flooring, compact CFL bulbs, and a boatload of cleaning and stripping products. If you've ever used Jasco to strip something and wandered around in a daze for two weeks, this is the place for you.   The owners and staff know what they're doing and are extremely helpful. Green products often require shifts in perspective and technique. I've always found the people here to be honest about the positives and challenges in working with materials (like pressed sorghum boards) that weren't readily available until a few years ago.   Tip: aka green is heavily involved in community events. Check the calendar at akagreen.com .   Four stars for innovative products, 1/2 star for above-and-beyond dialogue, and 1/2 star for thoughtful activism.

